				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">When the PPU is doing the dummy sprite pattern fetches for &quot;sprite $FF&quot;. Does anyone know which, if it is predictable, row of the sprite gets fetched?<br /><br />The reason I ask is that while it probably doesn't make a huge difference (or at the least, I'm not aware of anything that would care). But it does change what address is read. For example.<br /><br />In 8x16 sprite mode the possible addresses read are any value from:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">$1FE0 - $1FE7 or<br />$1FE8 - $1FFF<br /></div><br /><br />depending on if it is the first or second fetch<br /><br />In 8x8 mode, there are a bunch of possible options as well:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">$0FF0 - $0FF7 or $1FF0 - $1FF7<br />$0FF8 - $0FFF or $1FF8 - $1FFF<br /></div><br /><br />So this may just be an academic excessive, but does anyone know which row is fetched from this &quot;dummy sprite&quot;</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
